@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Vetex" where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed.

NOTE: I am not sure of this game's 'behaviour' on a stock 68000
      Amiga. For now, until somebody confirms that Vetex runs
      fine on a 68000 machine, this game will require an Amiga with
      a 68020 or faster processor... sorry!

                             How to play?

  To play, just click on a tile that is occupied by an 'X' shape
or a small coloured square that is linked to the empty tile and
the shape will move toward the empty tile. If an 'X' shape is
located on the clicked tile and a linked tile is occupied by
another 'X' shape, but there is no empty tile linked to the
clicked tile, the 'X' shape will go to the position occupied by
the other 'X' shape. Otherwise, the 'X' shape will go where the
empty tile is located...

  You can restart a game board, by clicking on the 'Replay'
button, but be aware that the amount of moves you make for the
current game board is added up until you complete it...

  Have fun!

  You can quit the game by clicking on the game window's close
button or by pressing on the 'Esc' key.

